          <div class="space-y-8 text-base md:text-lg text-[#4A4A4A] leading-loose font-medium pt-6 relative">
            <p>Money Memo started as an allowance log I made for my child.</p>
            <p>With a paper notebook, the notebook itself kept getting lost. And whenever a purchase went unrecorded, the balance never matched. Even saying "close enough is fine" didn't help — the mismatch itself was stressful. So I decided to lower the bar for recording instead.</p>
            <p>While building the app, I realized something: adults stumble in exactly the same places.</p>
            <p>It feels like a chore.<br />We forget.<br />And once the numbers stop matching, we quit.</p>
            <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold pt-4 text-center md:text-left leading-relaxed">
